    <body>
      <div type="edition" rend="break-none" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<div type="introduction" xml:lang="en">
	  <p>This edition is based on <ref target="bibl:N">Senart 1905-1906</ref>.</p>
	</div>
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  sidhaṃ otarāhasa <placeName key="pl:Dattāmitrī"><app
	    ><lem source="#N">dātā</lem>
	     <rdg source="#G #AS">daṃtā</rdg>
           </app>mitiyakasa</placeName> teṇakasa 
	   <persName key="pers:Dharmadeva">dhaṃmadeva</persName>putasa
	   <persName key="pers:Indrāgnidatta"><app
	     ><lem source="#N">īdrāgni</lem>
	      <rdg source="#G">iṃdrāgni</rdg>
	      <rdg source="#AS">īdāgni</rdg>
	   </app>datasa</persName>
	   dhaṃmātma<app
	     ><lem source="#N">nā</lem>
	      <rdg>
		<note xml:lang="sa">
		  <p>Senart notes: “The stroke which, rising perpendicularly,
		  makes the <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">ā</foreign> look
		  somewhat like <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">i</foreign>, 
		  is thinner and certainly accidental.”</p>
		</note>
	      </rdg>
	   </app>
	   <lb n="2"/>
	   <app>
	     <lem source="#N">imaṃ le</lem>
	     <rdg source="#G #AS">ima te</rdg>
	   </app>ṇaṃ pavate <placeName key="pl:Tiraṇhu">tiraṃṇhumhi</placeName>
	   khānitaṃ abhaṃtaraṃ ca leṇasa cetiyagharo <app
	     ><lem source="#N">poḍhiyo</lem>
	      <rdg source="#G">podhiṃyo</rdg>
	      <rdg source="#AS">poṃdhiyo</rdg>
	   </app> ca mātāpi<lb n="3" break="no"/>taro
	   udisa ima <app
	     ><lem source="#N">leṇa</lem>
	      <rdg source="#AS">leṇaṃ</rdg>
	   </app> kāritaṃ sava-budha-pujāya
	   cātudiśasa <app
	     ><lem source="#N">bhikhū</lem>
	      <rdg source="#G">bhikhu</rdg>
           </app>saṃghasa niyātitaṃ
	   sa<lb n="4" break="no"/>ha putena 
	   <persName key="pers:Dharmarakṣita">dhaṃmarakhitena</persName>
	</p> 
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>Success! (The gift) of <persName key="pers:Indrāgnidatta">Indrāgnidatta</persName>, son of <persName key="pers:Dharmadeva">Dharmadeva</persName>, the Yavana, a notherner from <placeName key="pl:Dattāmitrī">Dattāmitrī</placeName>. By him, inspired by true religion, this cave has bene caused to be excavated in mount <placeName key="pl:Tiraṇhu">Tiraṇhu</placeName>, and inside the cave a <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">caityagṛha</foreign> and cisterns. This cave made for the sake of his father and mother has been, in order to honour all Buddhas, bestowed on the universal <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">saṃgha</foreign> of monks, together with his son <persName key="pers:Dharmarakṣita">Dharmarakṣita</persName>.</p>
      </div>
